        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(nextcloud-talk): silently ignore non-message Talk events instead of returning 400",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nNextcloud Talk sends various event types (calls, system notifications, file shares) that may not have `object.type === \"Note\"` or `actor.type === \"Person\"`. The webhook handler's Zod schema was too strict — rejecting any payload that didn't match the exact message shape with a 400 \"Invalid payload format\" error.\n\nThis fix silently ignores non-matching payloads instead of returning 400, matching how other channel handlers gracefully handle unknown events.\n\nFixes #81566\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? (`No` — non-message events were already ignored after the 400 was returned; now they are silently acknowledged)\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? (`No`)\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? (`No`)\n",
